cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ARIA in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "ARIA: Causal-Aware Reasoning for Materials Discovery"
type: software
authors:
  - name: "ARIA Team"
    affiliation: "Johns Hopkins University"
repository-code: "https://github.com/yicao-elina/ARIA"
url: "https://github.com/yicao-elina/ARIA"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-02"
keywords:
  - materials-science
  - knowledge-graph
  - causal-reasoning
  - llm
  - rag
  - psp-hierarchy
abstract: >
  ARIA is a causal evidence-gating framework that helps LLMs reason over
  Processing-Structure-Property pathways for materials synthesis and property
  prediction. Unlike standard RAG, ARIA activates retrieved evidence only
  when it forms a causally complete PSP path.